1
00:00:00,691 --> 00:00:03,234
[footsteps]

2
00:00:03,734 --> 00:00:10,702
♪

3
00:00:12,324 --> 00:00:13,415
-It's here.
-No way.

4
00:00:13,826 --> 00:00:15,167
[KIGGITH]
What's so surprising?

5
00:00:15,247 --> 00:00:16,369
-[BOTH] Huh.
-We knew

6
00:00:16,459 --> 00:00:17,750
from eyewitness accounts

7
00:00:17,830 --> 00:00:19,752
it was hidden
somewhere in this area.

8
00:00:20,083 --> 00:00:21,254
Investigate it.

9
00:00:21,835 --> 00:00:22,926
What, you mean now?

10
00:00:23,296 --> 00:00:25,008
How do you expect us
to find anything?

11
00:00:25,088 --> 00:00:26,260
It's pitch black out.

12
00:00:26,430 --> 00:00:28,843
[KIGGITH] I didn't ask
for your opinion, did I?

13
00:00:29,013 --> 00:00:30,475
-Get to it.
-Fine.

14
00:00:31,265 --> 00:00:33,768
But before that, answer this.

15
00:00:34,229 --> 00:00:36,692
What is it that has you so
worked up tonight, Kiggith?

16
00:00:37,062 --> 00:00:39,275
That you'd ditch the hideout
we arranged for you?

17
00:00:40,646 --> 00:00:43,489
[KIGGITH] Do you not hear
its claws against the ground?

18
00:00:45,151 --> 00:00:46,282
[both gasp]

19
00:00:47,033 --> 00:00:48,034
[chuckles]

20
00:00:49,076 --> 00:00:51,078
Approaching near-silently,

21
00:00:51,579 --> 00:00:53,290
with its fangs bared.

22
00:00:53,961 --> 00:00:55,583
It's ready to pounce.

23
00:00:56,374 --> 00:00:58,586
That's the stride of a spider.

24
00:00:59,718 --> 00:01:01,720
-[birds chirping]
-[rooster crowing]

25
00:01:04,884 --> 00:01:09,479
♪

26
00:01:12,602 --> 00:01:14,024
[RUTI]
I go to sleep at night,

27
00:01:14,234 --> 00:01:15,856
and wake up to sunrise.

28
00:01:16,357 --> 00:01:17,818
The small joys in life.

29
00:01:17,988 --> 00:01:21,152
♪

30
00:01:21,322 --> 00:01:24,326
[grunting]

31
00:01:32,335 --> 00:01:33,506
[grunts]

32
00:01:33,626 --> 00:01:35,298
[creaking]

33
00:01:35,799 --> 00:01:37,801
[grunts]

34
00:01:39,423 --> 00:01:41,635
[grunts]

35
00:01:41,806 --> 00:01:46,020
♪

36
00:01:46,391 --> 00:01:48,773
[RUTI] Morning stretches
complete. Nice work.

37
00:01:49,184 --> 00:01:50,896
The brightness
of the morning sun.

38
00:01:52,398 --> 00:01:54,400
The satisfaction of exercise.

39
00:01:55,861 --> 00:01:57,904
The gleam
of a freshly-cleaned home.

40
00:01:58,444 --> 00:02:01,578
Simple pleasures I once thought
unnecessary as a Hero.

41
00:02:01,828 --> 00:02:04,992
But I get to experience them
now thanks to "New Truth,"

42
00:02:05,372 --> 00:02:07,375
the new Blessing
created within me.

43
00:02:07,875 --> 00:02:09,997
Almighty Demis
had nothing to do with it.

44
00:02:10,878 --> 00:02:13,051
Perhaps it's inaccurate
to call it his blessing,

45
00:02:13,922 --> 00:02:16,094
but more a power
born of my free will.

46
00:02:16,675 --> 00:02:18,137
At least,
that's what I believe.

47
00:02:18,467 --> 00:02:19,598
[clatters]

48
00:02:19,719 --> 00:02:21,430
Now this is the slow life.

49
00:02:21,931 --> 00:02:23,513
Morning, Mr. Crawly Wawly.

50
00:02:23,813 --> 00:02:25,605
[squawks]

51
00:02:25,896 --> 00:02:26,897
Hm?

52
00:02:27,017 --> 00:02:33,774
♪

53
00:02:34,195 --> 00:02:37,198
[water gurgling]

54
00:02:37,869 --> 00:02:41,123
♪

55
00:02:41,203 --> 00:02:43,586
[TISSE] The herb farm is really
coming along, isn't it?

56
00:02:44,417 --> 00:02:47,540
Yep. But I couldn't have
done it without you, Tisse.

57
00:02:48,041 --> 00:02:49,172
Are you sure about that?

58
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:51,174
Because I feel like
I haven't helped at all.

59
00:02:51,465 --> 00:02:53,297
This is still very new
to me, you know.

60
00:02:53,637 --> 00:02:55,639
That's why two heads
are better than one.

61
00:02:56,180 --> 00:02:57,181
[gasps]

62
00:02:57,351 --> 00:02:58,352
[chuckles]

63
00:02:59,934 --> 00:03:01,186
An herb garden, huh?

64
00:03:01,436 --> 00:03:03,148
I knew you were looking
to settle down,

65
00:03:03,228 --> 00:03:04,189
but I never expected you

66
00:03:04,269 --> 00:03:05,901
to think of something
like this.

67
00:03:07,483 --> 00:03:09,155
Adventuring's the side gig.

68
00:03:09,275 --> 00:03:11,778
But this project
will be my main job.

69
00:03:11,948 --> 00:03:13,740
Growing and tending
herbs full-time.

70
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:15,992
You're putting in this work
to help Red, right?

71
00:03:16,533 --> 00:03:18,245
[RUTI]
That's a big part of it, yeah.

72
00:03:18,415 --> 00:03:20,668
But mostly, doing something
that didn't involve

73
00:03:20,748 --> 00:03:23,381
swinging a sword around
seemed nice for a change.

74
00:03:24,923 --> 00:03:26,755
[chuckles]
It does, doesn't it?

75
00:03:27,586 --> 00:03:28,797
Um, about last night--

76
00:03:28,887 --> 00:03:30,389
[TISSE]
Okay, time to get to work!

77
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:33,432
[gasps] Oh, look!

78
00:03:37,096 --> 00:03:38,898
Figure it out, Mr. Crawly Wawly

79
00:03:39,269 --> 00:03:42,152
[chittering]

80
00:03:42,482 --> 00:03:44,945
Problem is the soil.
It's stone cold.

81
00:03:45,025 --> 00:03:46,107
To the touch.

82
00:03:46,657 --> 00:03:47,658
Why is that?

83
00:03:48,029 --> 00:03:50,361
This might require
another pair of eyes, milady.

84
00:03:50,992 --> 00:03:52,664
We should ask Red
to take a look.

85
00:03:54,957 --> 00:03:57,580
[RED] Seems like there's
cold mold growing under there.

86
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,001
[RUTI]
Cold mold?

87
00:03:59,542 --> 00:04:01,334
Like the stuff
that grows in caves?

88
00:04:01,424 --> 00:04:02,335
Yeah.

89
00:04:02,465 --> 00:04:04,467
It absorbs heat
from anything nearby.

90
00:04:05,338 --> 00:04:06,970
Normally only the huge colonies

91
00:04:07,050 --> 00:04:08,592
can cause problems
to adventurers,

92
00:04:09,093 --> 00:04:11,435
but on farmland,
all it takes is a trace amount

93
00:04:11,515 --> 00:04:12,847
for a disease to kick in.

94
00:04:13,438 --> 00:04:15,230
What you'd expect
starting a farm.

95
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,942
-Things go wrong.
-Hm.

96
00:04:18,273 --> 00:04:19,354
The good news is,

97
00:04:19,815 --> 00:04:22,318
because you noticed it
and came to me immediately,

98
00:04:22,738 --> 00:04:24,240
there's still time to fix this.

99
00:04:24,650 --> 00:04:26,362
-[Ruti gasps]
-Ready to get to work?

100
00:04:26,993 --> 00:04:27,824
Hm.

101
00:04:27,904 --> 00:04:29,706
Whatever it takes
to save the herbs.

102
00:04:30,287 --> 00:04:31,288
-Huh.
-[chitters]

103
00:04:31,578 --> 00:04:38,586
♪

104
00:05:01,943 --> 00:05:02,944
[RED]
Great work.

105
00:05:03,534 --> 00:05:06,157
If the chemicals we sprayed
get rid of the cold mold,

106
00:05:06,498 --> 00:05:08,250
the herbs should
recover in time.

107
00:05:08,951 --> 00:05:09,952
[RUTI]
Hmph.

108
00:05:10,412 --> 00:05:12,875
All we can do now is hope
for the herbs to pull through.

109
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:14,417
They will.

110
00:05:15,047 --> 00:05:16,799
-Thanks to your help.
-Hm.

111
00:05:18,712 --> 00:05:20,554
She's come a long way,
hasn't she?

112
00:05:21,305 --> 00:05:22,306
[RED]
You said it.

113
00:05:22,556 --> 00:05:23,637
Doing everything she can

114
00:05:23,717 --> 00:05:25,640
to save those little guys
she's caring for.

115
00:05:27,432 --> 00:05:30,105
To think we wouldn't have seen
this side of her as the Hero.

116
00:05:30,645 --> 00:05:33,569
Because she's finally free
to live at her own pace.

117
00:05:36,822 --> 00:05:38,114
So what about me?

118
00:05:48,836 --> 00:05:50,588
[RED]
The two of them will be fine.

119
00:05:51,088 --> 00:05:52,550
-[birds chirping]
-[rooster crowing]

120
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:54,052
[TISSE]
My name is Tisse.

121
00:05:54,592 --> 00:05:56,344
A member
of the Assassins' Guild,

122
00:05:56,755 --> 00:05:58,717
and an assassin
with a nefarious plan

123
00:05:58,807 --> 00:06:00,099
to oversleep this morning.

124
00:06:00,219 --> 00:06:01,891
Huh?
[gasps]

125
00:06:02,011 --> 00:06:03,893
[screams]

126
00:06:04,434 --> 00:06:06,105
[TISSE]
Um, good morning?

127
00:06:06,726 --> 00:06:09,019
Good morning. Any plans today?

128
00:06:09,399 --> 00:06:11,321
[TISSE]
Tending to the herbs, I guess.

129
00:06:11,572 --> 00:06:13,153
I took care of that already.

130
00:06:13,574 --> 00:06:14,575
Anything else?

131
00:06:14,735 --> 00:06:16,737
♪

132
00:06:17,078 --> 00:06:18,910
[TISSE]
Nothing in particular.

133
00:06:20,662 --> 00:06:21,663
Well, that's good.

134
00:06:21,743 --> 00:06:24,707
Because I want you
to accompany me today.

135
00:06:25,838 --> 00:06:27,039
Accompany you for what?

136
00:06:28,291 --> 00:06:30,093
[RUTI]
A very important task.

137
00:06:30,213 --> 00:06:33,847
♪

138
00:06:34,047 --> 00:06:37,181
[TISSE] Huh? Why are we having
breakfast like always?

139
00:06:37,721 --> 00:06:40,104
[water splashing]

140
00:06:44,189 --> 00:06:46,061
[TISSE]
And now we're taking a bath?

141
00:06:47,693 --> 00:06:48,694
[RUTI]
Tisse.

142
00:06:51,367 --> 00:06:52,738
[TISSE]
Um, yes?

143
00:06:53,369 --> 00:06:54,530
You like baths.

144
00:07:01,789 --> 00:07:03,671
[water splashing]

145
00:07:03,751 --> 00:07:05,633
I...like 'em enough

146
00:07:05,713 --> 00:07:07,465
to write my own
review book, sure.

147
00:07:08,046 --> 00:07:10,048
[RUTI] My brother's cooking
is the best in the world,

148
00:07:10,138 --> 00:07:11,139
isn't it?

149
00:07:12,341 --> 00:07:13,802
[TISSE]
Very best, sure.

150
00:07:14,143 --> 00:07:16,265
-[water splashing]
-So you get it.

151
00:07:16,976 --> 00:07:17,977
[TISSE]
Get what?

152
00:07:19,849 --> 00:07:21,231
Hook, line, and sinker.

153
00:07:21,561 --> 00:07:22,562
[chuckles]

154
00:07:23,814 --> 00:07:26,447
[TISSE] [gasps]
What is happening right now?

155
00:07:26,987 --> 00:07:29,991
[indistinct chatter]

156
00:07:32,784 --> 00:07:34,746
[TISSE]
An important task, huh?

157
00:07:35,207 --> 00:07:36,288
Did you know?

158
00:07:36,618 --> 00:07:38,751
My brother bought
my hairpin right here.

159
00:07:39,001 --> 00:07:41,003
That's very nice of him!
It's cute!

160
00:07:41,213 --> 00:07:42,214
Yep.

161
00:07:42,375 --> 00:07:45,048
♪

162
00:07:45,258 --> 00:07:47,010
[TISSE] [gasps]
Of course!

163
00:07:47,180 --> 00:07:49,132
Hairpin is code for
"This is a crime scene, Tisse,

164
00:07:49,222 --> 00:07:50,224
stay on your toes!"

165
00:07:51,014 --> 00:07:52,937
I mean, got it!
I'm on the lookout!

166
00:07:54,268 --> 00:07:55,269
Hm.

167
00:07:56,641 --> 00:07:58,273
-[TISSE] Hm.
-[townswoman 204A screams]

168
00:07:58,353 --> 00:08:00,275
-Hm.
-Runaway drake!

169
00:08:00,445 --> 00:08:03,449
[squawking]

170
00:08:04,780 --> 00:08:05,861
Guess I'll stop it.

171
00:08:06,032 --> 00:08:07,033
No.

172
00:08:07,323 --> 00:08:08,745
-I'll handle it.
-Wait.

173
00:08:09,245 --> 00:08:10,707
Won't you make it
a bigger scene?

174
00:08:12,078 --> 00:08:12,869
[thuds]

175
00:08:13,210 --> 00:08:14,371
Now, sit, boy.

176
00:08:15,662 --> 00:08:16,664
[whimpers]

177
00:08:17,254 --> 00:08:18,335
[TOWNSMAN 204B]
Out of all the trainers

178
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:20,758
it's nearly killed,
she's the one it listens to?

179
00:08:21,879 --> 00:08:24,222
She drew even more attention,
like I said.

180
00:08:25,514 --> 00:08:28,887
♪

181
00:08:29,018 --> 00:08:30,599
[RUTI]
The scenery here is pretty.

182
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:33,393
And it's always
so nice and breezy.

183
00:08:33,683 --> 00:08:35,435
[TISSE]
It is very nice, yes.

184
00:08:36,396 --> 00:08:38,899
[TISSE] So, is this where
the important task is?

185
00:08:41,492 --> 00:08:43,364
[TISSE] [gasps]
Milady?

186
00:08:45,907 --> 00:08:47,749
-[RUTI] You there.
-Hm? Huh?

187
00:08:48,289 --> 00:08:50,412
[RUTI] There's a monster
lying dormant underground.

188
00:08:50,702 --> 00:08:52,084
It needs to be dealt with.

189
00:08:52,254 --> 00:08:54,166
[MALE FARMER 204A]
Huh? What was that, miss?

190
00:08:54,507 --> 00:08:55,918
It's just a friendly warning,

191
00:08:56,048 --> 00:08:57,210
from someone here to help.

192
00:08:57,340 --> 00:08:58,341
[MALE FARMER 204A]
Huh?

193
00:08:58,421 --> 00:09:00,013
-[gasps]
-[male farmer 204A grunts]

194
00:09:00,714 --> 00:09:01,765
[male farmer 204A gasps]

195
00:09:02,806 --> 00:09:03,807
[explosion]

196
00:09:04,428 --> 00:09:06,020
[both shrieking]

197
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:07,932
So that's what she meant!

198
00:09:08,022 --> 00:09:10,224
This earthworm would've
devoured any human in sight

199
00:09:10,314 --> 00:09:11,436
after its hibernation!

200
00:09:12,437 --> 00:09:15,440
-Hi-yah.
-[chopping]

201
00:09:17,032 --> 00:09:18,484
-[thuds]
-[gasps]

202
00:09:19,445 --> 00:09:20,987
Oh. Wow!

203
00:09:21,077 --> 00:09:22,789
Pardon me, ma'am,
but are you Zoltan's

204
00:09:22,869 --> 00:09:25,332
very own strongest
adventurer, Miss Ruti?

205
00:09:25,662 --> 00:09:27,624
Anybody could've
executed that chop.

206
00:09:28,125 --> 00:09:30,497
Think of me as your friendly
neighborhood adventurer.

207
00:09:30,587 --> 00:09:32,460
You just split a man-eating
earthworm in two

208
00:09:32,550 --> 00:09:33,711
with your bare hands.

209
00:09:34,802 --> 00:09:35,843
[gasps]

210
00:09:36,054 --> 00:09:37,305
♪

211
00:09:37,385 --> 00:09:38,927
[indistinct chatter]

212
00:09:40,098 --> 00:09:41,760
[TISSE]
From the farm to the theater.

213
00:09:42,060 --> 00:09:43,472
What happened to the task?

214
00:09:44,393 --> 00:09:47,186
The lead actor has gotten
some rave reviews lately.

215
00:09:47,517 --> 00:09:48,608
This should be fun.

216
00:09:48,898 --> 00:09:50,820
Says here the play's based
on the story

217
00:09:50,901 --> 00:09:53,233
of a knight and a bandit
who fall for the same lady.

218
00:09:53,944 --> 00:09:55,656
Stop it, both of you!

219
00:09:55,736 --> 00:09:57,778
Haven't we been through
so much together?

220
00:09:58,619 --> 00:09:59,991
Oh, it's getting good,
isn't it?

221
00:10:00,832 --> 00:10:01,833
Isn't it?

222
00:10:01,913 --> 00:10:04,416
-[gasps]
-[indistinct chatter]

223
00:10:05,037 --> 00:10:06,168
[whimpering]

224
00:10:07,379 --> 00:10:08,921
That sword has been cursed.

225
00:10:09,291 --> 00:10:11,133
Toss it before
it's too late for you.

226
00:10:11,384 --> 00:10:13,006
Come try and take it from me!

227
00:10:13,386 --> 00:10:15,098
Ever since I got
my hands on this blade,

228
00:10:15,178 --> 00:10:17,391
my acting's been
nothing short of divine!

229
00:10:17,721 --> 00:10:21,355
Like, hell, I'm just gonna
throw all my dreams away!

230
00:10:21,435 --> 00:10:23,147
[female actress 204A screams]

231
00:10:23,437 --> 00:10:25,229
Possessed by a devil of arts.

232
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:28,944
He sacrificed his own lifespan
in exchange for this talent.

233
00:10:29,064 --> 00:10:32,067
-[gasps]
-[indistinct chatter]

234
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,242
I'm your friendly
neighborhood adventurer.

235
00:10:36,452 --> 00:10:37,533
Very ordinary.

236
00:10:38,324 --> 00:10:39,245
Plot twist!

237
00:10:39,325 --> 00:10:41,328
The rift between the bandit
and knight all started

238
00:10:41,418 --> 00:10:43,750
because of a devil hiding
in the mix this whole time!

239
00:10:44,131 --> 00:10:45,172
Huh?!

240
00:10:45,713 --> 00:10:47,465
The play isn't over just yet!

241
00:10:47,635 --> 00:10:48,836
Use this!

242
00:10:50,839 --> 00:10:52,260
O, brave adventurer!

243
00:10:52,510 --> 00:10:55,974
I beg you! Please rescue
the person I dearly love!

244
00:10:57,846 --> 00:10:59,849
[both grunt]

245
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,812
-[male actor 204A grunts]
-[swords clanging]

246
00:11:03,903 --> 00:11:05,695
[male actor 204A grunting]

247
00:11:05,775 --> 00:11:08,028
And now she's drawing
even more attention.

248
00:11:08,358 --> 00:11:11,532
This will be a play to remember
for everyone in the audience.

249
00:11:11,702 --> 00:11:13,164
-[swords clanging]
-[male actor 204A groans]

250
00:11:16,708 --> 00:11:18,670
[dog howling]

251
00:11:21,293 --> 00:11:23,506
You sure gave out
a bunch of autographs.

252
00:11:23,626 --> 00:11:25,378
I wasn't trying
to draw attention.

253
00:11:25,508 --> 00:11:28,762
I hear rumors of a production
starring the Adventurer Ruti

254
00:11:28,842 --> 00:11:30,223
that's premiering tomorrow.

255
00:11:31,935 --> 00:11:32,936
Yay.

256
00:11:33,187 --> 00:11:34,478
-[OPARARA] Order up!
-[chuckles]

257
00:11:35,139 --> 00:11:36,390
[TISSE]
Can't be too surprised.

258
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,603
You're well-known
around Zoltan these days.

259
00:11:38,813 --> 00:11:41,025
And it's not like
the attention is malicious.

260
00:11:41,646 --> 00:11:44,199
I know. But today
was important to me.

261
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,902
What's so important
that you had me

262
00:11:46,992 --> 00:11:48,454
tag along with you, anyway?

263
00:11:48,534 --> 00:11:49,535
♪

264
00:11:49,956 --> 00:11:50,957
[sighs]

265
00:11:52,248 --> 00:11:54,080
[TISSE]
Oh. Not often do I see her,

266
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:55,252
look so down.

267
00:11:55,412 --> 00:11:56,713
The day's not over yet.

268
00:11:57,044 --> 00:11:58,415
We can turn this around.

269
00:11:58,625 --> 00:12:00,007
-Can we?
-Yeah.

270
00:12:04,302 --> 00:12:05,974
So, how are things lately?

271
00:12:21,191 --> 00:12:23,113
Anything or anyone
bothering you?

272
00:12:23,864 --> 00:12:26,037
Ooh, well, for starters,

273
00:12:26,117 --> 00:12:27,949
I am a little worried
about how weird

274
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:29,160
you've been acting.

275
00:12:31,122 --> 00:12:32,204
[RUTI]
It's hopeless.

276
00:12:32,834 --> 00:12:35,167
Hey. Talk to me,
what's the matter?

277
00:12:35,547 --> 00:12:36,548
[sighs]

278
00:12:37,089 --> 00:12:37,960
Huh?

279
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:39,672
Something's been
on your mind lately,

280
00:12:39,762 --> 00:12:41,054
but I don't know what it is.

281
00:12:41,384 --> 00:12:43,927
Today was supposed to help you
decompress for a bit.

282
00:12:44,387 --> 00:12:46,219
-[gasps]
-[RUTI] A day to relax,

283
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,852
A day where I treat you
to your favorite oden,

284
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:50,604
and you tell me whatever's
bothering you.

285
00:12:50,725 --> 00:12:52,316
All of that, just for me?

286
00:12:52,687 --> 00:12:55,150
[RUTI]
Yep. But it didn't go too well,

287
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,611
I think.

288
00:12:58,654 --> 00:13:00,446
[TISSE] Everything
from the drake to the demon

289
00:13:00,536 --> 00:13:03,289
seemed inconsequential
to someone as strong as her.

290
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:06,703
Causing a scene
was the last thing on her mind.

291
00:13:07,624 --> 00:13:09,586
She acts funny sometimes.

292
00:13:10,047 --> 00:13:11,208
Still...

293
00:13:12,169 --> 00:13:13,921
You're a very nice person,
milady.

294
00:13:14,341 --> 00:13:16,173
But all I do is make
a mess of things,

295
00:13:16,254 --> 00:13:18,136
leaving you to clean
up the aftermath.

296
00:13:18,426 --> 00:13:20,428
Is that what's been
bothering you today?

297
00:13:21,139 --> 00:13:23,352
♪

298
00:13:23,512 --> 00:13:25,144
I tried to be ordinary.

299
00:13:25,264 --> 00:13:27,356
I used the most
ordinary skills.

300
00:13:27,767 --> 00:13:29,769
I even said
I was very ordinary.

301
00:13:29,939 --> 00:13:31,441
[TISSE] There's
your problem right there.

302
00:13:33,113 --> 00:13:34,114
Really?

303
00:13:34,404 --> 00:13:37,157
Cheer up! If you ask me,
you're much better off now.

304
00:13:37,237 --> 00:13:39,410
Are you implying you thought
I was worse than this?

305
00:13:39,490 --> 00:13:40,491
Huh?!

306
00:13:41,993 --> 00:13:43,835
Let's just say I nearly
tore my hair out

307
00:13:43,915 --> 00:13:45,627
when you tossed that knight
off the bridge.

308
00:13:45,707 --> 00:13:46,708
Who?

309
00:13:47,749 --> 00:13:49,591
[both laugh]

310
00:13:50,172 --> 00:13:52,425
[TISSE]
Thank you very much, Miss Ruti.

311
00:13:53,005 --> 00:13:54,507
No need to worry about me.

312
00:13:55,638 --> 00:13:57,260
It'll all be over by morning.

313
00:14:04,058 --> 00:14:05,309
-What are you doing?
-Huh.

314
00:14:06,110 --> 00:14:07,402
[WOLF]
Airship's been looked over,

315
00:14:07,482 --> 00:14:09,114
so we're finishing
up the report.

316
00:14:10,315 --> 00:14:12,367
[paper rustling]

317
00:14:13,278 --> 00:14:16,702
Omit any information on Tisse.
Redo the draft.

318
00:14:16,872 --> 00:14:19,245
Sorry, Kiggith, but there's
no way that's happening.

319
00:14:19,415 --> 00:14:21,287
Bottom line is,
it's important stuff.

320
00:14:21,417 --> 00:14:22,919
If Tisse's here in Zoltan,

321
00:14:22,999 --> 00:14:24,331
it could only mean
that the airship

322
00:14:24,421 --> 00:14:25,963
belongs to the Hero Ruti.

323
00:14:26,924 --> 00:14:28,796
And omitting
crucial information

324
00:14:29,086 --> 00:14:31,389
would be an act of treachery
against Cardinal Ljubo.

325
00:14:32,971 --> 00:14:33,932
[slashing]

326
00:14:34,262 --> 00:14:36,344
[thudding]

327
00:14:37,265 --> 00:14:39,098
[KIGGITH] I can't
have you reporting this.

328
00:14:39,768 --> 00:14:42,151
Even if it means treachery
against the Church,

329
00:14:42,231 --> 00:14:44,984
my score to settle with Tisse
is far more important.

330
00:14:47,817 --> 00:14:49,529
♪

331
00:14:50,110 --> 00:14:51,742
[crow cawing]

332
00:14:53,113 --> 00:14:54,075
[paper rustling]

333
00:14:54,165 --> 00:14:56,167
[KIGGITH]
Long have I waited for you,

334
00:14:57,118 --> 00:14:58,750
my old enemy.

335
00:14:58,830 --> 00:15:05,838
♪

336
00:15:13,016 --> 00:15:14,438
Didn't expect you here.

337
00:15:15,098 --> 00:15:16,310
Kiggith Viper.

338
00:15:17,021 --> 00:15:19,103
[KIGGITH] Brings back
old memories of our days

339
00:15:19,193 --> 00:15:21,396
training under Master
when I see you standing

340
00:15:21,486 --> 00:15:22,647
beneath the moonlight.

341
00:15:23,027 --> 00:15:24,319
Tisse Garland.

342
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:26,702
The Assassins' Guild
has only one way

343
00:15:26,782 --> 00:15:28,153
of dealing with deserters.

344
00:15:28,494 --> 00:15:30,326
Meaning you know
what comes next.

345
00:15:30,996 --> 00:15:32,708
I trust you're aware of that?

346
00:15:32,959 --> 00:15:35,502
[scoffs]
That bloodlust in your eyes.

347
00:15:35,832 --> 00:15:38,665
No wonder our master saw
great potential in you.

348
00:15:39,256 --> 00:15:42,129
Which means killing you now
would be a crying shame.

349
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:43,721
What are you implying?

350
00:15:43,881 --> 00:15:44,882
[KIGGITH]
Come on.

351
00:15:44,972 --> 00:15:47,635
Leave Zoltan behind
and join up with me.

352
00:15:47,765 --> 00:15:50,639
You have what it takes
to work at my side, Tisse.

353
00:15:51,019 --> 00:15:52,981
And what about the two men
who were with you?

354
00:15:53,392 --> 00:15:54,393
I killed them.

355
00:15:54,683 --> 00:15:56,816
Just like I'd kill anyone
who would dare stand

356
00:15:56,896 --> 00:15:58,608
between me
and my greatest prey.

357
00:15:58,738 --> 00:16:00,320
Well, that makes it
much easier for me

358
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,152
to cut you down
right here and now.

359
00:16:02,612 --> 00:16:05,195
Traitors of the Guild
will not walk away unpunished.

360
00:16:05,446 --> 00:16:06,577
Rousing words.

361
00:16:06,657 --> 00:16:08,289
Yet all I see is a girl lacking

362
00:16:08,369 --> 00:16:10,041
an assassin's
thirst for murder.

363
00:16:11,953 --> 00:16:13,875
As your fellow student
and mentor,

364
00:16:13,955 --> 00:16:16,508
I'll show you what it means
to be an assassin.

365
00:16:16,758 --> 00:16:20,883
♪

366
00:16:21,013 --> 00:16:22,014
[thuds]

367
00:16:22,515 --> 00:16:23,886
-[slashing]
-[grunts]

368
00:16:24,097 --> 00:16:28,642
♪

369
00:16:28,722 --> 00:16:30,144
-[swords clanging]
-[grunts]

370
00:16:31,856 --> 00:16:33,067
-[swords clanging]
-[gasps]

371
00:16:34,228 --> 00:16:35,229
[laughing]

372
00:16:36,691 --> 00:16:38,363
-[grunts]
-[gasps]

373
00:16:38,533 --> 00:16:43,579
♪

374
00:16:43,869 --> 00:16:44,910
Not bad.

375
00:16:45,451 --> 00:16:47,203
But how will you
deal with these?

376
00:16:49,496 --> 00:16:50,497
[gasps]

377
00:16:50,627 --> 00:16:52,669
♪

378
00:16:52,749 --> 00:16:54,711
[rumbling]

379
00:16:55,052 --> 00:16:56,053
[gasps]

380
00:16:56,754 --> 00:16:58,756
-Huh.
-More where that came from.

381
00:16:58,966 --> 00:17:01,059
Dodge them, and this airship
will get torn apart

382
00:17:01,139 --> 00:17:02,260
piece by piece.

383
00:17:02,510 --> 00:17:05,313
What good is the airship to you
if it's not in one piece?

384
00:17:05,474 --> 00:17:08,107
That technique is reckless
and kills innocent bystanders.

385
00:17:08,397 --> 00:17:10,069
Master forbade us
from using it!

386
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:13,363
See, that right there
is what I'm talking about!

387
00:17:13,483 --> 00:17:15,235
You lack the thirst for murder.

388
00:17:15,365 --> 00:17:17,657
Our Blessing grants us
the right to fight and kill

389
00:17:17,738 --> 00:17:19,029
without any restraint.

390
00:17:19,199 --> 00:17:22,413
That realization is why I left
the Assassins' Guild!

391
00:17:23,374 --> 00:17:25,336
-[grunts]
-[explosions]

392
00:17:26,087 --> 00:17:27,248
-[clinks]
-[gasps]

393
00:17:27,338 --> 00:17:28,920
-[explosion]
-[gasps]

394
00:17:30,592 --> 00:17:31,593
[swords clanging]

395
00:17:33,966 --> 00:17:35,217
[TISSE]
He's changed.

396
00:17:36,599 --> 00:17:39,222
He used to be more faithful
to his Assassin's Blessing

397
00:17:39,302 --> 00:17:40,303
than I was.

398
00:17:41,014 --> 00:17:43,056
So why did he end up like this?

399
00:17:44,228 --> 00:17:45,649
-Huh.
-Got you!

400
00:17:45,980 --> 00:17:47,652
[explosions]

401
00:17:47,942 --> 00:17:49,233
Huh?
[groans]

402
00:17:50,114 --> 00:17:51,276
[groaning]

403
00:17:51,736 --> 00:17:52,867
[thuds]

404
00:17:53,448 --> 00:17:56,452
[groaning]

405
00:17:57,493 --> 00:17:58,534
It's over.

406
00:17:58,704 --> 00:18:00,626
Any last words before you die?

407
00:18:01,377 --> 00:18:04,000
Wait.
You want answers, don't you?

408
00:18:04,421 --> 00:18:05,712
I'm in the employ

409
00:18:05,962 --> 00:18:08,255
of Cardinal Ljubo
of the Church.

410
00:18:08,715 --> 00:18:10,427
Kill me,
and you're in the dark.

411
00:18:10,758 --> 00:18:11,759
[gasps]

412
00:18:13,721 --> 00:18:16,224
How could you spill
your client's name like that?

413
00:18:16,554 --> 00:18:18,346
I'll tell you everything
I know.

414
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:20,349
I swear it on my life,
all right?

415
00:18:20,689 --> 00:18:22,731
So, please,
just have mercy on me.

416
00:18:23,732 --> 00:18:26,526
Ljubo wants to utilize...

417
00:18:26,606 --> 00:18:27,907
[TISSE]
He refuses to uphold

418
00:18:27,987 --> 00:18:30,991
even the most fundamental rules
of being an assassin.

419
00:18:31,822 --> 00:18:34,865
This sniveling man is nothing
more than a dirty murderer!

420
00:18:35,916 --> 00:18:38,920
[groaning]

421
00:18:40,712 --> 00:18:41,713
Ah...

422
00:18:41,963 --> 00:18:47,930
♪

423
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:50,433
[TISSE] Kiggith could only
adhere to his Blessing.

424
00:18:52,265 --> 00:18:53,977
He had no will of his own.

425
00:18:55,348 --> 00:18:58,352
[birds chirping]

426
00:19:01,605 --> 00:19:02,857
[sighs]
Miss Ruti.

427
00:19:04,319 --> 00:19:06,071
-[RUTI] Are you done here?
-[TISSE] Yes.

428
00:19:06,701 --> 00:19:07,863
He was a rogue assassin

429
00:19:07,953 --> 00:19:09,655
who deserted
the Assassins' Guild.

430
00:19:10,656 --> 00:19:11,657
[RUTI]
I see.

431
00:19:12,458 --> 00:19:13,459
[TISSE]
This isn't well known,

432
00:19:13,539 --> 00:19:15,872
but the Guild
isn't as authoritarian

433
00:19:15,962 --> 00:19:17,503
as people seem to think it is.

434
00:19:18,294 --> 00:19:19,666
You're allowed
to turn down missions

435
00:19:19,756 --> 00:19:20,797
you don't want to take.

436
00:19:21,338 --> 00:19:22,840
You're even free to retire.

437
00:19:23,921 --> 00:19:26,133
Through Blessings,
we walk as assassins,

438
00:19:26,223 --> 00:19:27,475
and need sanctuary.

439
00:19:28,306 --> 00:19:29,978
Somewhere we can
help each other.

440
00:19:30,478 --> 00:19:32,521
That sanctuary,
and that organization,

441
00:19:32,601 --> 00:19:33,852
is the Assassins' Guild.

442
00:19:34,733 --> 00:19:37,817
Really? The reputation
makes the Guild seem scary.

443
00:19:38,437 --> 00:19:39,939
Smart marketing, is all.

444
00:19:40,319 --> 00:19:41,901
Even down to the rule
about declining

445
00:19:41,991 --> 00:19:43,323
unreasonable missions.

446
00:19:43,783 --> 00:19:45,365
Call it a strategy of sorts.

447
00:19:45,495 --> 00:19:47,788
We can't be disciplined
if we have just cause.

448
00:19:48,248 --> 00:19:51,332
We're all just doing everything
we can to live out our lives.

449
00:19:53,915 --> 00:19:56,257
So you're not allowed
to murder without a reason?

450
00:19:56,458 --> 00:19:57,589
No, of course not.

451
00:19:57,919 --> 00:20:00,763
Think of the chaos we'd cause
if we killed left and right!

452
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:04,967
♪

453
00:20:05,057 --> 00:20:07,140
At the end of the day,
it's still killing.

454
00:20:07,470 --> 00:20:08,932
And I made you, a Hero,

455
00:20:09,022 --> 00:20:11,104
help carry out
an assassination.

456
00:20:11,395 --> 00:20:13,938
And is that why you wouldn't
talk to me about it, Tisse?

457
00:20:14,278 --> 00:20:16,901
I know you want to live
a peaceful life here in Zoltan

458
00:20:16,981 --> 00:20:18,613
more than anything! But me?

459
00:20:18,733 --> 00:20:22,287
♪

460
00:20:22,407 --> 00:20:23,408
My Blessing.

461
00:20:23,619 --> 00:20:24,620
My fate being tied

462
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:26,492
to the cruel life
of an assassin.

463
00:20:28,204 --> 00:20:29,545
I'm honestly not sure

464
00:20:29,625 --> 00:20:32,298
I even have the right to stay
by your side anymore.

465
00:20:32,418 --> 00:20:35,132
♪

466
00:20:35,252 --> 00:20:37,634
Assassin or not,
you're still my close friend.

467
00:20:37,845 --> 00:20:39,136
Stay by my side.

468
00:20:39,597 --> 00:20:40,558
As you are.

469
00:20:40,678 --> 00:20:42,720
And if it'd truly
make you happier,

470
00:20:43,471 --> 00:20:46,104
you can always choose to become
a slow-life assassin.

471
00:20:47,265 --> 00:20:49,688
What in the world
is a slow-life assassin?

472
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,361
Huh?

473
00:20:55,525 --> 00:20:57,277
That's a funny thing to say.

474
00:20:57,487 --> 00:20:59,950
No matter what happens,
I'll continue to support you

475
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:01,201
whenever you need it.

476
00:21:01,582 --> 00:21:03,584
Who cares if we're Hero
and Assassin?

477
00:21:04,084 --> 00:21:05,586
I'll do it because I want to.

478
00:21:05,706 --> 00:21:07,458
[sniffles]
Miss Ruti.

479
00:21:08,169 --> 00:21:11,172
[crying]

480
00:21:12,384 --> 00:21:13,345
[RUTI]
Starting today,

481
00:21:14,046 --> 00:21:15,597
let's open up
more to each other.

482
00:21:16,258 --> 00:21:17,970
[TISSE]
Okay. You're right.

483
00:21:18,761 --> 00:21:19,852
Thank you!

484
00:21:19,932 --> 00:21:22,896
♪

485
00:21:30,404 --> 00:21:33,908
[LJUBO] Huh. Unusually
shoddy work for Kiggith.

486
00:21:34,279 --> 00:21:36,822
This doesn't even tell me
the airship's location.

487
00:21:37,372 --> 00:21:39,204
He'll need to lead me
there in person.

488
00:21:41,827 --> 00:21:43,749
Nevertheless,
this at least confirms

489
00:21:43,830 --> 00:21:45,251
the airship's existence.

490
00:21:45,461 --> 00:21:46,883
Summon Van back to me.

491
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:48,174
[MALE UNDERLING 204A]
Understood.

492
00:21:48,675 --> 00:21:49,716
No, wait.

493
00:21:50,047 --> 00:21:51,799
On second thought, I'll go.

494
00:21:52,339 --> 00:21:53,681
[MALE UNDERLING 204A]
Need you go personally?

495
00:21:53,931 --> 00:21:57,055
The trip to Zoltan will proceed
once I meet with Van.

496
00:21:57,845 --> 00:22:00,098
[LJUBO] Noble aims
need time to cultivate,

497
00:22:00,188 --> 00:22:03,442
and at long last,
mine has come to fruition.

498
00:22:14,614 --> 00:22:16,617
[ESTA] The Church's warriors
can no longer keep up

499
00:22:16,707 --> 00:22:18,209
with the way Van fights.

500
00:22:20,872 --> 00:22:22,293
Our party is in shambles.

501
00:22:22,714 --> 00:22:23,835
We should descend.

502
00:22:24,125 --> 00:22:26,428
What reason is there to leave
if I can keep fighting?

503
00:22:26,928 --> 00:22:29,261
Because if we don't leave now,
then they'll all die.

504
00:22:29,722 --> 00:22:30,763
Is that a problem?

505
00:22:31,223 --> 00:22:32,264
Are you serious?

506
00:22:32,345 --> 00:22:34,597
Only the Hero is destined
to save the world.

507
00:22:35,268 --> 00:22:38,482
Therefore, any sacrifices
made under the Hero's Blessing

508
00:22:38,732 --> 00:22:40,604
are justified
for the greater good.

509
00:22:40,944 --> 00:22:42,106
That's where you're wrong.

510
00:22:42,196 --> 00:22:43,027
[MALE SOLDIER 204A]
Flare sighted!

511
00:22:43,147 --> 00:22:44,358
Prepare to descend!

512
00:22:48,613 --> 00:22:49,955
[VAN]
Cardinal Ljubo's orders?

513
00:22:50,155 --> 00:22:53,248
At last, finally
my real adventure can begin.

514
00:22:54,159 --> 00:22:56,162
Do you have no gentle
words of support

515
00:22:56,252 --> 00:22:58,004
to send off
our fallen comrades?

516
00:22:58,254 --> 00:22:59,916
[VAN]
Glance not behind, Hero.

517
00:23:00,416 --> 00:23:02,008
From texts on Heroes of old,

518
00:23:02,088 --> 00:23:03,590
and words I cherish most.

519
